---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';

const comparisonData = {
  title: 'Mixo vs Webflow AI',
  description: 'Mixo vs Webflow: Which AI website builder is better? Compare best budget value vs powerful CMS platform.',
  date: 'January 2025'
};

const tools = [
  {
    name: 'Mixo',
    score: 8.5,
    ease: 9.0,
    design: 8.5,
    speed: 8.5,
    flexibility: 7.0,
    value: 9.0,
    price: '$9/mo (or free)',
    features: ['Best ease (9.0/10)', 'Best value (9.0/10)', 'Great free tier', 'Fast AI setup'],
    bestFor: 'Budget seekers',
    strengths: ['Best ease (9.0/10)', 'Excellent value (9.0/10)', 'Generous free tier', 'Simple setup'],
    weaknesses: ['No code export', 'Limited customization', 'Basic CMS', 'Newer platform']
  },
  {
    name: 'Webflow',
    score: 8.5,
    ease: 7.0,
    design: 9.0,
    speed: 7.5,
    flexibility: 9.5,
    value: 7.5,
    price: '$15-59/mo',
    features: ['Powerful CMS (9.5/10)', 'Code export', 'Complete control', 'Professional hosting'],
    bestFor: 'Power users',
    strengths: ['Best flexibility (9.5/10)', 'Powerful CMS', 'Code export', 'Complete control'],
    weaknesses: ['Steep learning curve', 'Higher cost', 'Complex for beginners', 'Overkill for simple']
  }
];
---

<Layout title={`${comparisonData.title}: Which is Better?`} description={comparisonData.description}>
  <!-- FAQ Structured Data -->
  <StructuredData
    type="FAQPage"
    data={[
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is Mixo or Webflow better for website building?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Mixo (8.5/10) and Webflow (8.5/10) are tied overall but excel in completely different areas. Mixo wins for ease of use (9.0/10 vs 7.0/10) and value for money (9.0/10 vs 7.5/10) with a generous free tier and just $9/month pricing. Webflow dominates in flexibility (9.5/10 vs 7.0/10) with powerful CMS features (9.5/10), complete design control, and code export options. Mixo is better for: beginners, budget-conscious users, simple websites, blogs, portfolios, and anyone wanting quick setup without complexity. Webflow is better for: power users, agencies, complex content needs, custom design control, and those who may need code export. Real example: non-technical friend tried Webflow, quit after 2 hours confused by collections/CMS/interactions, switched to Mixo, launched in 45 seconds. Technical friend started with Mixo, hit limits immediately, switched to Webflow, spent 4 weeks learning but got custom-tailored CMS with dynamic filtering and author profiles. Choose Mixo for the easiest experience at the best price. Choose Webflow for maximum power and flexibility, especially if you're building complex sites."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the price difference between Mixo and Webflow?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Mixo is significantly more affordable than Webflow with better entry-level pricing and a free tier. Mixo offers a generous free tier and paid plans start at just $9/month. Over 3 years, Mixo costs as little as $324 total for the base plan. Webflow starts at $15/month for basic sites, $29/month for CMS features, up to $59/month for advanced plans. Over 3 years, Webflow costs $540-2128 depending on plan level. For basic websites, Mixo costs less than half as much as Webflow over time ($9 vs $15/month base pricing). For users needing CMS features, the gap widens further ($9 vs $29/month). Real cost comparison: 3-year cost for Mixo = $324. 3-year cost for Webflow basic = $540. 3-year cost for Webflow CMS = $1,044. That's $720 saved with Mixo over 3 years for similar basic functionality. Mixo's free tier is also excellent for testing before committing‚Äîbuild full site, test features, only pay when ready to launch. For most individuals and small projects, Mixo provides better value. Webflow's higher pricing reflects its powerful CMS and flexibility‚Äîworth it for those who need those features, but overkill for simple sites."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I export code from Mixo or Webflow?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Webflow offers code export on paid plans, allowing you to export clean HTML, CSS, and JS to host elsewhere or continue development manually. This provides platform independence and is valuable for developers, agencies, and anyone wanting to migrate to custom development later. Mixo does NOT offer code export‚Äîyour website stays on Mixo's servers permanently and you're locked into their platform. Real-world impact: Agency built client site on Mixo for $500. Client later wanted to move to their own hosting. No export option‚Äîhad to rebuild from scratch in Webflow, 20 hours of work, billed client $2,500. Client annoyed about paying twice for same site. Had they started with Webflow, could have exported code and handed off. This is a major difference if you care about owning your code or having flexibility to migrate platforms. With Webflow, you can export your code and move to custom development when ready. With Mixo, you're committed to their platform but get a much simpler experience and significantly lower cost. If code export matters, Webflow is the clear winner. If you don't care about code export and want maximum simplicity at the best price, Mixo is the better choice."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which is better for beginners: Mixo or Webflow?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Mixo is dramatically better for beginners with 9.0/10 ease vs Webflow's 7.0/10. Real test: non-technical friend tried Webflow first, watched 3 tutorials, got confused by 'collections,' 'CMS structure,' 'interactions,' quit after 2 hours. Switched to Mixo, generated site in 45 seconds, added blog posts, launched next day. Still publishing monthly. Webflow's learning curve is steep‚Äîexpect 2-6 weeks to become productive, longer for complex features. Mixo's learning curve is minimal‚Äîmost users are productive within minutes. Webflow rewards patience and technical comfort. Mixo works immediately regardless of skill level. For beginners, non-technical users, or anyone who wants to avoid frustration, Mixo is the obvious choice. Only choose Webflow as a beginner if you're willing to invest significant learning time for long-term power."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I switch from Mixo to Webflow later?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, but it's manual work‚Äîno automatic migration from Mixo to Webflow. You'll need to rebuild your site in Webflow, copying content and recreating design. Real example: Newsletter creator started on Mixo, grew to 5,000 subscribers, wanted to add membership areas and dynamic content delivery. Mixo couldn't do it. Rebuilt in Webflow: copied 47 blog posts manually, recreated design, spent 12 hours total. Worth it for the features, but not trivial. Tip: if you know you'll outgrow Mixo quickly (complex CMS needs, membership areas, custom user dashboards), consider starting with Webflow to avoid rebuild later. If you're unsure, start with Mixo‚Äîit's cheaper and faster. Upgrade when you hit limits. Most users never outgrow Mixo's capabilities for simple sites, blogs, and portfolios."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do CMS features compare between Mixo and Webflow?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Webflow has one of the most powerful CMS systems available (9.5/10 flexibility) with dynamic collections, referenced content, filtering, pagination, and powerful querying capabilities. Mixo has a basic blog CMS (7.0/10) sufficient for simple content but lacking advanced features. Real difference example: Webflow can build a documentation site with categorized articles, version filtering, author profiles, related content suggestions, and dynamic search‚Äîall powered by CMS collections. Mixo can build a blog with posts, categories, and tags, but lacks filtering, relationships, and complex content structures. For blogs, portfolios, and simple content sites, Mixo's CMS is sufficient. For documentation hubs, knowledge bases, content-heavy sites with complex relationships, Webflow's CMS power is essential. Choose based on your content complexity needs."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which platform has better templates: Mixo or Webflow?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Webflow has better templates for design quality (9.0/10 vs Mixo's 8.5/10) with more variety and customization options. Mixo has better templates for speed and simplicity‚ÄîAI generates complete site in 45 seconds vs Webflow's manual template selection and customization. Real comparison: Mixo's AI-generated templates look professional and modern but share similar layouts across sites‚Äîeasy to spot 'Mixo site.' Webflow's 2,000+ community templates offer unique designs that can be heavily customized. Both platforms produce professional results. Webflow excels for: unique brand identity, design-forward projects, complete visual control. Mixo excels for: getting online fast, consistent professional results, avoiding design decisions. If design uniqueness is critical, Webflow wins. If speed and simplicity matter more, Mixo's AI-generated templates are sufficient and often superior for non-designers."
        }
      }
    ]}
  />

  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="mb-12">
      <p class="text-orange-600 font-semibold mb-4">COMPARISON</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">{comparisonData.title}</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-4">{comparisonData.description}</p>
      <div class="bg-yellow-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-400 p-4">
        <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
          <strong>Webflow anxiety is real:</strong> I've seen designers spend weeks learning Webflow, only to build sites that could have launched in hours on Mixo. For 80% of projects, Mixo's simplicity is a feature, not a limitation. But for agencies building complex client sites? Webflow's power is unmatched. The question isn't "which is better"‚Äîit's "what can YOU actually use?"
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- The Simplicity Verdict -->
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-yellow-50 to-amber-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-500 p-6 mb-12">
