            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-medium">Learning Curve</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50 font-bold">Minimal</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">Steep</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-medium">Setup Speed</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50 font-bold">Very fast (8.5/10)</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">Moderate (7.5/10)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-medium">Target User</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50 font-bold">Beginners, everyone</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50 font-bold">Power users, designers</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-medium">Best For</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50 font-bold">Simple sites, value</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50 font-bold">Complex sites, power</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Deep Dive -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">The Key Differences</h2>

      <div class="mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Simplicity vs. Power</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
          <strong>Mixo maximizes simplicity.</strong> Easy setup, minimal learning, great for beginners.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>Webflow maximizes power.</strong> Complete control with steep learning curve.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Value Proposition</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
          <strong>Mixo is budget-friendly.</strong> $9/mo with generous free tier.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>Webflow is premium.</strong> Higher cost for professional features.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Code Export</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
          <strong>Webflow offers portability.</strong> Export code for custom development.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>Mixo is hosted-only.</strong> Your site stays on Mixo permanently.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">CMS Capabilities</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
          <strong>Webflow has powerful CMS.</strong> 9.5/10 flexibility for complex content.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>Mixo has basic CMS.</strong> Sufficient for simple sites, blogs, portfolios.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- My Experience -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-sky-50 to-blue-50 border-[3px] border-sky-300 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">My Experience: Beginner vs. Pro</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold">Real testing, not theoretical comparison</p>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Two friends. Both starting newsletters. Similar content needs. Completely different technical comfort levels.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>Friend A (non-technical):</strong> Tried Webflow first. Watched 3 tutorials. Got confused by "collections," "CMS structure," "interactions." Quit after 2 hours. Switched to Mixo. Generated site in 45 seconds. Added blog posts. Launched next day. Still publishing monthly.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>Friend B (technical):</strong> Started with Mixo. Hit limits immediately. "I can't customize the layout. The blog structure is too simple. I need more control." Switched to Webflow. Learning curve was steep but 4 weeks later, she had a custom-tailored CMS with dynamic filtering, author profiles, related content‚Äîeverything she wanted.</p>
          <div class="bg-sky-100 border-l-[4px] border-sky-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-sky-900 font-medium"><strong>The outcomes:</strong> Friend A is paying $9/month, happy with Mixo. Friend B is paying $29/month, happy with Webflow. Both chose right for their skills.</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>Then the migration test:</strong> Friend A's newsletter grew. Wanted to add membership areas, custom user dashboards, dynamic content delivery. Mixo couldn't do it. Would require rebuilding in Webflow anyway.</p>
          <div class="bg-green-100 border-l-[4px] border-green-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-green-900 font-medium"><strong>The reality:</strong> Mixo is perfect until it isn't. Great for starters, but you'll outgrow it. Webflow has a steeper entry but a much higher ceiling.</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>The lesson:</strong> Mixo for "I just need a site that works" - beginners, simple blogs, landing pages, MVPs. Webflow for "I need to build something custom" - power users, complex CMS, agencies, client work. If you don't know whether you need Webflow's power, you probably don't.</p>
          <div class="bg-amber-100 border-l-[4px] border-amber-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-amber-900 font-medium"><strong>The truth:</strong> Mixo gets 80% of users 80% of the way there for 30% of the cost. Webflow is for the 20% who hit Mixo's limits. Start with Mixo. Upgrade to Webflow when you outgrow it.</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">I've used both extensively. Mixo is delightfully simple but limited. Webflow is frustratingly complex but unlimited. The right choice depends entirely on your skills and needs.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  <!-- REAL USER PLATFORM STORIES -->
